The role of academic conference in scientific communication. Efficiency of the conference for the doctoral student.
To pass the course, PhD students have to present a paper at an academic conference. The students reflect critically upon their conference experience in a 10-minute presentation at a doctoral seminar. In addition, the students present in written form the abstract of their conference paper and the materials used in the conference presentation (slides, handouts, full text of the presentation, etc). The conference experience has to be different from that presented in the course SOSS.00.007.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The objective of the course is to provide an opportunity to discuss critically one's real experience of participating in an academic conference and to increase the effectiveness of participating in next conferences.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The students acquire the skills of critical analysis of academic conference, their own presentation and the feedback they received to the paper.
